[:CompletionPopupMenu]
=== Completion Popup Menu (`C-mouse-3') ===

: [[image:drew-emacs-icicle-mouse-3-menu]]
: '''This Candidate''' submenu:
::: [[image:drew-emacs-icicle-mouse-3-This-Candidate]]
: '''Sorting''' submenu:
::: [[image:drew-emacs-icicle-mouse-3-Sorting]]
: '''Save/Retrieve''' submenu:
::: [[image:drew-emacs-icicle-mouse-3-Save-Retrieve]]
: '''Sets''' submenu:
::: [[image:drew-emacs-icicle-mouse-3-Sets]]
: '''Toggle/Cycle/Change''' submenu:
::: [[image:drew-emacs-icicle-mouse-3-Toggle]]
: '''Miscellaneous''' submenu:
::: [[image:drew-emacs-icicle-mouse-3-Misc]]


Contextual menu '''Completion''' pops up when you use `C-mouse-3' in buffer `*Completions*'.  Some of its menu items apply to the clicked candidate; others apply to all candidates.  See [[Icicles - Completions Display]].







[:FileIciclesMenu]
=== File Menu: Icicles Submenu ===
: [[image:drew-icicles-File-submenu]]

'''Icicles''' augments the standard '''File''' menu, adding an '''Icicles''' submenu that provides [[multi-command]]s and specialized [[Dired]] commands.







[:EditIciclesMenu]
=== Edit Menu: Icicles Submenu ===
: [[image:drew-icicles-Edit-submenu]]

'''Icicles''' augments the standard '''Edit''' menu, adding an '''Icicles''' submenu.







[:BookmarksIciclesMenu]
=== Bookmarks Menu: Icicles Submenu ===
: [[image:drew-icicles-Bookmarks-submenu]]

'''Icicles''' augments the standard '''Bookmarks''' menu (typically a submenu of the '''Edit''' menu), adding an '''Icicles''' submenu that provides [[multi-command]]s for navigating to and among different kinds of bookmarks or markers.  The bookmark and tags menu items are avaible only if you also use '''[[Bookmark+]]''', but the go-to items are always available.









[:SearchIciclesMenu]
=== Search Menu: Icicles Submenu ===
: [[image:drew-icicles-Search-submenu]]

'''Icicles''' augments the standard '''Search''' menu (typically a submenu of the '''Edit''' menu), adding an '''Icicles''' submenu that provides [[multi-command]]s for searching files and [[buffer]]s in various ways. 






[:OptionsAndCustomizeIciclesMenus]
[:OptionsIciclesMenu]
=== Options Menu: Icicles Submenu ===
: [[image:DrewsEmacsIciclesOptionsMenu]]

'''Icicles''' augments the standard '''Options''' menu. It adds an '''Icicles''' submenu with items that let you modify specific '''Icicles''' options.






[:CustomizeEmacsIciclesMenu]
=== Customize Emacs Menu: Icicles Submenu ===

: [[image:DrewsEmacsIciclesOptionsCustomizeMenu]]

'''Icicles''' also adds an '''Icicles''' submenu to the '''Customize Emacs''' submenu of menu '''Options''', with operations for customizing anything.  See [[Icicles - Customization and General Tips]].








[:FramesIciclesMenu]
=== Frames Menu: Icicles Submenu ===
: [[image:drew-icicles-Frames-submenu]]

If you use library <tt>[[menu-bar+.el]]</tt> then you have a '''Frames''' menubar menu.  '''Icicles''' augments this menu, adding an '''Icicles''' submenu that provides [[multi-command]]s affecting [[frame]]s.  If you do not use library ##menu-bar+.el## then the same menu items are added to the main '''Icicles''' menu.














[:CustomizeIciclesKeys]
=== Customize Buffer for Icicle Mode Keys ===
: [[image:IciclesCustomizingKeys]]

You can easily customize the ''Icicle'' mode [[key binding]]s for top-level commands, without knowing any EmacsLisp.
See [[Icicles - Key Bindings#icicle-top-level-key-bindings|Customizing Keys]].









[:AproposCompletion]
=== Apropos Completion (Regexp Matching) ===

[[image:IciclesRegexpCompletions]]

Buffer `*Completions*' shows all matches for your input `##M-x ise.*char##'. See [[Icicles - Nutshell View]].








[:AproposCompletionCycling]
=== Apropos Completion Cycling ===

[[image:iciclesscreenshot]]

See [[Icicles - Apropos Completions]] and [[Icicles - Cycling Completions]].








[:ModeLine]
=== Mode-Line ===

This screenshot shows highlighting of the `Icy' [[mode line]] lighter that indicates ''Icicle'' mode.  

: [[image:DrewsEmacsIcyModeLine]]

The fact that `Icy' is highlighted at all indicates that [[completion]] is available. The light-green background and the `##+##' indicate [[multi-command]] completion. And the blue box (which appears as an underline and overline) indicates that completion is currently ''strict'': your input must match one of the candidates.










[:Minibuffer]
=== Minibuffer ===

[[image:IciclesMinibufRegion1]]
[[image:IciclesMinibufRegion2]]

These screenshots show the effect of options `icicle-point-position-in-candidate' and `icicle-mark-position-in-candidate' on the placement of the [[cursor]] during candidate [[Icicles - Cycling Completions|cycling]].  

They also show one of the states of the [[Icicles - Nutshell View#CompletionStatusIndicators|completion status indicator]], just to the left of the prompt:

* Presence of the indicator means that you can use [[completion]].
* The blue box means that completion is ''strict'' (your input must match some candidate).
* The '''`##+##'''' with the green highlight behind it mean that the current command is a [[Icicles - Multi-Commands | multi-command]].

[[image:DrewsEmacsMinibufLevel1]]

This screenshot shows [[progressive completion]].  See [[Icicles - Customization and General Tips]] and [[Icicles - Nutshell View]].







